<section xml:id="C13.S18">
<title>Relations to Other Functions</title>         
<subsection xml:id="C13.S18.SS1">
<title>Elementary Functions</title>        
 
 
<para xml:id="C13.S18.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C13.S18.SS1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="13.18.1" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E1">M_{0,\frac{1}{2}}\left(2z\right)=2\sinh z,</Math> <Math equation-number="13.18.2" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E2">M_{\kappa,\kappa-\frac{1}{2}}\left(z\right)=W_{\kappa,\kappa-\frac{1}{2}}\left (z\right)=W_{\kappa,-\kappa+\frac{1}{2}}\left(z\right)=e^{-\frac{1}{2}z}z^{ \kappa},</Math> <Math equation-number="13.18.3" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E3">M_{\kappa,-\kappa-\frac{1}{2}}\left(z\right)=e^{\frac{1}{2}z}z^{-\kappa}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C13.S18.SS2">
<title>Incomplete Gamma Functions</title>        
     
<para xml:id="C13.S18.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C13.S18.SS2.p1.s1">
For the notation see §§6.2(i), 7.2(i), and8.2(i).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C13.S18.SS2.p1.s2">
When <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C13.S18.SS2.p1.m1">\tfrac{1}{2}-\kappa\pm\mu</Math> is an integer the Whittaker functions can be expressed as incomplete gamma functions (or generalized exponential integrals).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C13.S18.SS2.p1.s3">
For example, <Math equation-number="13.18.4" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E4">M_{\mu-\frac{1}{2},\mu}\left(z\right)=2\mu e^{\frac{1}{2}z}z^{\frac{1}{2}-\mu} \gamma\left(2\mu,z\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="13.18.5" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E5">W_{\mu-\frac{1}{2},\mu}\left(z\right)=e^{\frac{1}{2}z}z^{\frac{1}{2}-\mu} \Gamma\left(2\mu,z\right).</Math>
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C13.S18.SS2.p1.s4">
Special cases are the error functions <Math equation-number="13.18.6" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E6">M_{-\frac{1}{4},\frac{1}{4}}\left(z^{2}\right)=\tfrac{1}{2}e^{\frac{1}{2}z^{2} }\sqrt{\pi z}\operatorname{erf}\left(z\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="13.18.7" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E7">W_{-\frac{1}{4},\pm\frac{1}{4}}\left(z^{2}\right)=e^{\frac{1}{2}z^{2}}\sqrt{ \pi z}\operatorname{erfc}\left(z\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C13.S18.SS3">
<title>Modified Bessel Functions</title>            
 
<para xml:id="C13.S18.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C13.S18.SS3.p1.s1">
When <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C13.S18.SS3.p1.m1">\kappa=0</Math> the Whittaker functions can be expressed as modified Bessel functions.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C13.S18.SS3.p1.s2">
For the notation see §§10.25(ii) and9.2(i).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C13.S18.SS3.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="13.18.8" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E8">M_{0,\nu}\left(2z\right)=2^{2\nu+\frac{1}{2}}\Gamma\left(1+\nu\right)\sqrt{z}I _{\nu}\left(z\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="13.18.9" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E9">W_{0,\nu}\left(2z\right)=\sqrt{\ifrac{2z}{\pi}}K_{\nu}\left(z\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="13.18.10" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E10">W_{0,\frac{1}{3}}\left(\tfrac{4}{3}z^{\frac{3}{2}}\right)=2\sqrt{\pi}z^{\frac{ 1}{4}}\mathrm{Ai}\left(z\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C13.S18.SS4">
<title>Parabolic Cylinder Functions</title>          
 
<para xml:id="C13.S18.SS4.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C13.S18.SS4.p1.s1">
For the notation see §12.2.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C13.S18.SS4.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="13.18.11" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E11">W_{-\frac{1}{2}a,\pm\frac{1}{4}}\left(\tfrac{1}{2}z^{2}\right)=2^{\frac{1}{2}a }\sqrt{z}U(a,z),</Math> , <Math equation-number="13.18.12" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E12">M_{-\frac{1}{2}a,-\frac{1}{4}}\left(\tfrac{1}{2}z^{2}\right)=2^{\frac{1}{2}a-1 }\Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{2}a+\tfrac{3}{4}\right)\sqrt{\ifrac{z}{\pi}}\*\left(U \left(a,z\right)+U\left(a,-z\right)\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="13.18.13" mode="display" xml:id="C13.S18.E13">M_{-\frac{1}{2}a,\frac{1}{4}}\left(\tfrac{1}{2}z^{2}\right)=2^{\frac{1}{2}a-2} \Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{2}a+\tfrac{1}{4}\right)\sqrt{\ifrac{z}{\pi}}\*\left(U \left(a,-z\right)-U\left(a,z\right)\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
